<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-22T09:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-22T09:41:00-05:00" n="892" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d892">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/7098</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-22T16:00:00+01:19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.52 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4057. My 2890, August 8, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d892fn1">Not
                                printed.</note> Minister for Foreign Affairs informs me that
                            according to article 4 of declaration of neutrality war vessels and
                            vessels assimilated thereto, such as armed merchantmen, belonging to
                            belligerent countries are excluded as general rule from the Netherlands
                            territory including colonial possessions. Following exceptions to rule
                            are recognized: <list>
                                <label>(1)</label>
                                <item>Vessels of above classes may enter Netherlands territorial
                                    waters in case of shipwreck or storm; must leave as soon as
                                    circumstances permit.</item>
                                <label>(2)</label>
                                <item>Vessels of this description may enter ports of Dutch colonial
                                    possessions for sole purpose of completing supply of provision
                                    and coal but must leave as soon as purpose has been accomplished
                                    and at any rate within 24 hours.</item>
                                <label>(3)</label>
                                <item>Such vessels if destined for a religious, scientific, or
                                    philanthropic mission are not affected by rule of
                                    exclusion.</item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>